Poison control centers in the US are reporting a nearly 400 percent increase in the number of children under the age of 12 swallowing alcohol-based hand sanitizer, according to the Georgia Poison Center.
according to dr Gaylord Lopez, director of the Georgia Poison Center, cases of hand sanitizer use among children under 12 years old, poison control centers report, increased from 3,266 in 2010 to 16,117 in 2014.
&quot;Kids are getting more and more access to these products, and unfortunately, a percentage of them end up going to the emergency room,&quot; Lopez told CNN.
He said some kids drink sanitizer on purpose, while some do it to impress their friends or for a dare on social media.
Videos on YouTube show youngsters drinking sanitizer just for a cheap experience.
