The Berlin school administration has found that only a few refugee parents send their children to day care centers, an estimated ten to 15 percent: &quot;For the uprooted parents, it is first of all very important to keep the family together,&quot; says Ilja Koschembar, spokesman for young people and families in the Berlin Senate Administration.
