Not a diet fruit - Mangoes are high in sugar
Mangoes are exotic and juicy-sweet.
But if you want to keep your slim figure in mind, you are often advised not to use them.
Because mangoes contain a relatively large amount of sugar - especially sucrose.
The exotic fruits are still healthy: they contain B vitamins as well as vitamins E and C. Above all, mangoes contain a lot of vitamin A and its precursor beta-carotene.
Those who eat the fruit thus support their eyesight, immune system and metabolic processes in the body.
When bought, mangoes should not be too soft or too firm and should smell pleasant.
Skin color alone doesn&#39;t tell you how ripe the fruit is - so green mangoes can taste delicious too.
They should be stored at room temperature and consumed within a few days.
Then they taste naturally pure or in sweet dishes.
A mango also gives hearty dishes a special touch.
It softens the slightly bitter taste of some leafy salads such as chicory and radicchio.
And a mango chutney goes well with fish, poultry, lamb and game.
